main event: Four objects were observed in the sky over Taiwan for approximately 4.5 minutes during a military report on 14 July 1965.
interesting points: The objects varied in appearance and course,Three other objects were observed at different intervals for varying lengths of time,The report concluded that the objects resembled a satellite or aircraft,No physical evidence was collected or photos taken,Observers consisted of military personnel with experience in visual identification.
witness description: military personnel with visual observation experience
